BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
First we use the graph to identify two points. We find [`([$x[0]], [$y[0]])`] and [`([$x[1]], [$y[1]])\text{,}`] but you might find another pair of points and the slope will work out to be the same. Using the slope formula:

[```\newcommand{\amp}{&}
\begin{aligned}
m \amp= \frac{y_2 - y_1}{x_2 - x_1}\\
\amp= \frac{[$top]}{[$bottom]}\\
\amp= \frac{[$top->reduce]}{[$bottom->reduce]}
\end{aligned}
```]

So the slope is [`[$m]\text{.}`]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

